    "content": "<p>Assertion (A) Among the two $$\\mathrm{O}-\\mathrm{H}$$ bonds in $$\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}$$ molecule, the energy required to break the first $$\\mathrm{O}-\\mathrm{H}$$ bond and the other $$\\mathrm{O}-\\mathrm{H}$$ bond is same.</p>\n<p>Reason (R) This is because the electronic environment around oxygen is the same even after breakage of one $$\\mathrm{O}-\\mathrm{H}$$ bond.</p>",
